<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-21T03:58:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-21T03:58:00-05:00" n="787" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d787">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1167</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Odessa</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RJA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Odessa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-21T11:00:00+02:02"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            21, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 27, 9.51
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>After three days’ battle between the Little Russians and Maximalists
                                aided by the fleet which bombarded the city Odessa remains under the
                                control of the Maximalists. The Americans are uninjured.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_RJA1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Ray</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>